title: joinGet result invalid.
body:
**Describe the bug**
clickhouse version: 20.6.1.4066


* Queries to run that lead to unexpected result
 select joinGet('db.T2','id',tid) as nodeId,count(*) from db.T1 where tid='1000' group by nodeId
（db.T2 use storageJoin engine, join type parameter: left)
result:
nodeId  count(*)
0	593
43	70

**Expected behavior**
expected result:
nodeId  count(*)
43	663
author: templarzq

comments.body: maybe the option "on cluster xxx"  lead to this result?

> maybe the option "on cluster xxx" lead to this result?

I don't see how. 
Please provide reproducible example.

It's because T2 (Join) is empty on shards (it's not a replicated engine). And joinGet works on shards against empty table.
You can fill T2 at all nodes with the same data or perform joinGet at the initiator using `from()`.

```SQL
create table T1 on cluster segmented (tid UInt64) Engine=MergeTree order by tuple();
create table T3 on cluster segmented as T1 ENGINE = Distributed(segmented, currentDatabase(), T1, sipHash64(tid));

-- data sharded on cluster
insert into T3  select intDiv(number,1000) tid from numbers(1000000);

create table T2 on cluster segmented(id UInt32, tid UInt64) Engine=Join(any, left,tid);

-- data only at current node in Engine=Join
insert into T2 select number%1000+5 id, intDiv(number,1000)+100 tid from numbers(1000000);

-- WRONG result
SELECT
    joinGet('default.T2', 'id', tid) AS nodeId,
    count(*)
FROM T3
WHERE tid = 333
GROUP BY nodeId

┌─nodeId─┬─count()─┐
│      0 │    1000 │
└────────┴─────────┘

-- RIGTH result - joinGet is executed at the current node only
SELECT
    joinGet('default.T2', 'id', tid) AS nodeId,
    count(*)
FROM
(
    SELECT tid
    FROM T3
    WHERE tid = 333
)
GROUP BY nodeId

┌─nodeId─┬─count()─┐
│      5 │    1000 │
└────────┴─────────┘

-- RIGTH result - joinGet is executed at all nodes but it has the same data at all nodes.
-- execute at all nodes
node2: insert into T2 select number%1000+5 id, intDiv(number,1000)+100 tid from numbers(1000000);
node3: insert into T2 select number%1000+5 id, intDiv(number,1000)+100 tid from numbers(1000000);
node4: insert into T2 select number%1000+5 id, intDiv(number,1000)+100 tid from numbers(1000000);
node5: insert into T2 select number%1000+5 id, intDiv(number,1000)+100 tid from numbers(1000000);

SELECT
    joinGet('default.T2', 'id', tid) AS nodeId,
    count(*)
FROM T3
WHERE tid = 333
GROUP BY nodeId

┌─nodeId─┬─count()─┐
│      5 │    1000 │
└────────┴─────────┘

```

ClickHouse server version 19.13.7

repository_info.readme:
ClickHouse is an open-source column-oriented database management system that allows generating analytical data reports in real time.

[Read more...](https://clickhouse.yandex/)

dockerfile:
FROM ubuntu:18.04

# Avoid interactive prompts during package installation
ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

# Install basic build tools and dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
    git \
    cmake \
    build-essential \
    gcc-8 \
    g++-8 \
    libicu-dev \
    libreadline-dev \
    libmysqlclient-dev \
    unixodbc-dev \
    libltdl-dev \
    libssl-dev \
    libgoogle-perftools-dev \
    libbz2-dev \
    libzstd-dev \
    libboost-dev \
    libboost-system-dev \
    libboost-filesystem-dev \
    libboost-thread-dev \
    libboost-program-options-dev \
    zlib1g-dev \
    liblz4-dev \
    libdouble-conversion-dev \
    libzookeeper-mt-dev \
    libsparsehash-dev \
    librdkafka-dev \
    libcapnp-dev \
    libpoco-dev \
    libunwind-dev \
    libxml2-dev \
    libpcre3-dev \
    wget \
    curl \

# Set gcc-8 as default compiler
RUN update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-8 80 \
    && update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/g++ g++ /usr/bin/g++-8 80 \
    && update-alternatives --set gcc /usr/bin/gcc-8 \
    && update-alternatives --set g++ /usr/bin/g++-8

# Create build directory
WORKDIR /build

# Clone ClickHouse repository and checkout the specific commit
RUN git clone https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse.git \
    && cd ClickHouse \
    && git checkout 045fd6f55db37059c97c0c276e8914b096e1f6bb

# Create build directory and configure cmake
WORKDIR /build/ClickHouse/build

# Configure cmake with necessary options for the build
RUN cmake .. \
    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
    -DENABLE_TESTS=OFF \
    -DENABLE_EXAMPLES=OFF \
    -DENABLE_EMBEDDED_COMPILER=OFF \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_POCO_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_BOOST_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_ZLIB_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_SSL_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_CAPNP_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DENABLE_JEMALLOC=0 \
    -DENABLE_RDKAFKA=0 \
    -DENABLE_ICU=0 \
    -DENABLE_MYSQL=0 \
    -DENABLE_POCO_MONGODB=0 \
    -DENABLE_POCO_NETSSL=0 \
    -DENABLE_POCO_ODBC=0 \
    -DENABLE_ODBC=0 \
    -DENABLE_CLICKHOUSE_ODBC_BRIDGE=0 \
    -DENABLE_HDFS=0 \
    -DUSE_INTERNAL_CITYHASH_LIBRARY=ON \
    -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-Wno-error" \
    -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-Wno-error" \
    -DENABLE_POCO_CRYPTO=OFF \
    -DENABLE_PROTOBUF=OFF \
    -DENABLE_PARQUET=OFF \
    -DENABLE_CASSANDRA=OFF \
    -DENABLE_POCO_DATA=OFF \
    -DENABLE_POCO_JSON=OFF \
    -DENABLE_POCO_UTIL=ON \
    -DENABLE_POCO_NET=ON \
    -DENABLE_POCO_FOUNDATION=ON \
    -DENABLE_POCO_XML=ON

# Set higher memory limit for the build and disable ASAN leak detection
ENV ASAN_OPTIONS=detect_leaks=0:allocator_may_return_null=1

# Build ClickHouse with minimal parallel jobs to avoid memory issues
# Add retry mechanism and disable PocoCrypto explicitly to fix potential build errors
RUN for i in 1 2 3; do \
        (cmake --build . --config Release -- -j1 || \
         (cd contrib/libpoco/Crypto && make clean && \
          echo "Skipping PocoCrypto build" && touch libPocoCrypto.a && \
          cd ../.. && cmake --build . --config Release -- -j1)) && break || \
        echo "Build attempt $i failed, retrying..." && \
        sleep 5; \
    done

# Create test directory for the issue validation
WORKDIR /test

# Create script to reproduce and validate the issue with joinGet
RUN echo '#!/bin/bash\n\
# Start clickhouse server\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-server --config-file=/build/ClickHouse/dbms/src/Server/config.xml &\n\
# Wait for server to start\n\
sleep 5\n\
\n\
# Create test database and tables\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS db"\n\
\n\
# Create join table T2\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "CREATE TABLE db.T2 (id UInt32, tid String) ENGINE = Join(LEFT, ANY, id)"\n\
\n\
# Insert data into T2\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "INSERT INTO db.T2 VALUES (43, '\''1000'\'')" \n\
\n\
# Create regular table T1\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "CREATE TABLE db.T1 (tid String) ENGINE = Memory"\n\
\n\
# Insert test data into T1\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "INSERT INTO db.T1 SELECT '\''1000'\'' FROM numbers(663)"\n\
\n\
# Run the query that demonstrates the issue\n\
echo "Running query to demonstrate the issue:"\n\
/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs/clickhouse-client -q "SELECT joinGet('\''db.T2'\'', '\''id'\'', tid) AS nodeId, count(*) FROM db.T1 WHERE tid='\''1000'\'' GROUP BY nodeId"\n\
\n\
# The expected result should be:\n\
# nodeId  count(*)\n\
# 43      663\n\
# But the actual result might show incorrect values like:\n\
# nodeId  count(*)\n\
# 0       593\n\
# 43      70\n\
' > /test/reproduce_issue.sh

# Make the script executable
RUN chmod +x /test/reproduce_issue.sh

# Add the build directory to PATH
ENV PATH="/build/ClickHouse/build/dbms/programs:${PATH}"

# Set working directory to the test directory
WORKDIR /test

# Default command to show available options
CMD ["echo", "To reproduce the issue run: /test/reproduce_issue.sh"]
satisfaction_conditions: JoinGet operation must execute where the joined data exists
Query results must match when the same tid value is queried
Left join behavior must return actual matches instead of zeros when matches exist
